  <brief_title>Feeding Bottle Design, Milk Intake and Infant Growth</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Institute of Child Health</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Institute of Child Health</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      It is increasingly recognised that rapid growth in infancy may be associated with a greater
      risk of cardiovascular disease later in life. This trial will investigate whether the use of
      infant feeding bottles with different designs influences the milk intake and growth of
      infants. We will compare the growth of bottle-fed infants with that of a breast-fed reference
      group.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
